page.title: 02 London Nautical:05310180
page.content: London Nautical Secondary School is located in sq km 05310180 which includes Blackfriars Station and Bridge in the north, a power station to the east and the National Theatre to the west. The primary land cover in this sq km is commercial, consisting of private offices, many of which are new, high-rise developments, employing 1000s of people. A substantial part of the square is being re-developed. This mainly involves demolishing old offices and warehouses and erecting new offices, car parking space and some council housing. The Coin Street re-development scheme, near to the London Nautical School, is a current example. The River Thames takes up a large amount of space in our sq km and so is considered to be a secondary land cover.
